                                                                                                               Tatas close Citi buy
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, Dec. 31: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) today announced that it had completed the acquisition of Citigroup Incs interest in Citigroup Global Services Ltd (CGSL), the captive business process outsourcing (BPO) firm, for an all-cash consideration of $512 million.        
	Citi has also signed an agreement for TCS to provide process outsourcing services to the bank and its affiliates for an aggregate amount of $2.5 billion over nine years.        
	According to TCS, the acquisition will broaden its portfolio of end-to-end IT and BPO services in the global banking and financial services sector. With CGSL in its bag, TCS now becomes the countrys second largest BPO.         
	CGSL now offers various services that include transaction processing, customer services, collections and risk management.        
	N. Chandrasekaran, COO and executive director of TCS, said: This acquisition gives us the ability to offer an end-to-end, domain-led third-party solution for business operations to our large financial services clients.                                                                                                                                        
